  "chapter": {
    "number": 10,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Retribution for Israel’s Sin"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Israel was a luxuriant vine,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "yielding fruit for himself.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The more his fruit increased,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the more he increased the altars.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The better his land produced,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the better he made the sacred pillars.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Their hearts are devious;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "now they must bear their guilt.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The LORD will break down their altars",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and demolish their sacred pillars.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely now they will say,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“We have no king,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for we do not revere the LORD.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "What can a king do for us?”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They speak mere words;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with false oaths they make covenants.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "So judgment springs up",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like poisonous weeds in the furrows of a field.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The people of Samaria will fear",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for the calf of Beth-aven.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2487
          },
          {
            "text": "Indeed, its people will mourn",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with its idolatrous priests—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "those who rejoiced in its glory—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for it has been taken from them into exile.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Yes, it will be carried to Assyria",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as tribute to the great king.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2488
          },
          {
            "text": "Ephraim",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2489
          },
          {
            "text": "will be seized with shame;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Israel will be ashamed of its wooden idols.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2490
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Samaria will be carried off with her king",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a twig on the surface of the water.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The high places of Aven",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2491
          },
          {
            "text": "will be destroyed—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "it is the sin of Israel;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "thorns and thistles will overgrow their altars.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Then they will say to the mountains, “Cover us!”",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and to the hills, “Fall on us!”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2492
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Since the days of Gibeah you have sinned, O Israel,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and there you have remained.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Did not the battle in Gibeah",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "overtake the sons of iniquity?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2493
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will chasten them when I please;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nations will be gathered against them",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to put them in bondage",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for their double transgression.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Ephraim is a well-trained heifer that loves to thresh;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but I will place a yoke on her fair neck.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will harness Ephraim, Judah will plow,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and Jacob will break the hard ground.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Sow for yourselves righteousness",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and reap the fruit of loving devotion;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "break up your unplowed ground.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For it is time to seek the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "until He comes and sends righteousness",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "upon you like rain.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You have plowed wickedness and reaped injustice;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you have eaten the fruit of lies.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Because you have trusted in your own way",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and in the multitude of your mighty men,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "the roar of battle will rise against your people,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that all your fortresses will be demolished",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "as Shalman devastated Beth-arbel",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in the day of battle,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "when mothers were dashed to pieces",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "along with their children.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Thus it will be done to you, O Bethel,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because of your great wickedness.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "When the day dawns,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the king of Israel will be utterly cut off.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 2487,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Beth-aven means house of wickedness. This is a derogatory term for Bethel, which means house of God; see 1 Kings 12:28–29.",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 10,
          "verse": 5
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 2488,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Or to King Jareb",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 10,
          "verse": 6
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 2489,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "That is, the northern kingdom of Israel; also in verse 11",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 10,
          "verse": 6
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 2490,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Or of its own counsel",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 10,
          "verse": 6
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 2491,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Or of wickedness; Aven is a reference to Beth-aven (a derogatory term for Bethel); see verse 5.",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 10,
          "verse": 8
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 2492,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Cited in Luke 23:30; see also Revelation 6:16.",
        "reference": {
